'''Zilubostam''' ({{lang-fa|<U+0632><U+064A><U+0644><U+0648><U+0628><U+0633><U+0637><U+0627><U+0645>}}, also [[Romanize]]d as '''Z<U+012B>l<U+016B>bos<U+1E6D><U+0101>m''') is a village in [[Howmeh-ye Sarpol Rural District]], in the [[Central District (Sarpol-e Zahab County)|Central District]] of [[Sarpol-e Zahab County]], [[Kermanshah Province]], [[Iran]]. At the 2006 census, its population was 48, in 9 families.<ref>{{IranCensus2006|05}}</ref>  

